At CEATEC in Japan, an amazing project was presented, inspiring the Nissan engineers from bumblebees to create new accident-avoiding systems.
In cooperation with Tokyo University, Nissan has built the BR23C biomimetic system controlled by car robots, a mini-car equipped with the characteristics of bees, with the aim of supporting the development of a system that avoids any collisions.
