While the bees are open to endless possibilities to avoid other bees, the researchers could only use the rotational movement, or acceleration and deceleration, to avoid other bees.
The BR23C contains lithium polymer batteries that are lighter and more energy-efficient, and therefore have a longer lifespan than conventional lithium-ion batteries.
Andoh explained, it depends on the instinctive, intelligent response, and less on the processing of the data, and even less on the ability to save it.
This device only needs to process a few inputs per second and react to them accordingly.
It does not have to save them, or produce an intuitive, logical reaction based on previous maneuvers, so that it only uses a handful of KB memory.
There is no need for gigabyte and megabytes severe memories.
This is the first step in the development of immediate collision avoidance technology, which Nissan believes will be in production as standard within the next ten years.
